3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX calculates SUI/USDT funding rates hourly based on the price divergence between perpetual and spot markets. The Starknet-based settlement system ensures transparent rate calculations while off-chain matching provides fast execution without gas costs. Funding payments are automatically settled between long and short positions every hour, with rates typically ranging from -0.01% to 0.01% depending on market sentiment toward SUI."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SUI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI/USDT on RabbitX presents unique arbitrage opportunities due to the DEX's smaller user base creating occasional rate inefficiencies compared to centralized exchanges. The Layer 1 blockchain token's volatility combined with RabbitX's zero gas fee structure makes it attractive for high-frequency funding rate strategies."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical SUI Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI funding rates on RabbitX have shown distinct patterns correlating with network development milestones and DeFi ecosystem growth. During periods of high SUI ecosystem activity, funding rates tend to skew positive as traders take long positions anticipating price appreciation. The hourly settlement frequency on RabbitX means rate changes occur more frequently than traditional 8-hour cycles, creating additional arbitrage windows. Historical data shows SUI rates on RabbitX occasionally deviate 0.02-0.05% from major CEX rates due to the platform's smaller liquidity pool."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"DEX Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX's position as an early-stage DEX creates regular funding rate arbitrage opportunities between it and established centralized exchanges trading SUI perpetuals. The platform's cross-margin system allows efficient capital utilization when executing arbitrage strategies across multiple positions. Zero gas fees for trading operations significantly improve arbitrage profitability compared to other DEX perpetual platforms. Traders can exploit rate differentials by going long on RabbitX when rates are negative while shorting on CEXs with positive rates, capturing the spread without transaction costs."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations for RabbitX SUI Trading"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The primary risk stems from RabbitX's limited user base and smaller liquidity pools, which can lead to higher slippage during volatile SUI price movements. As an early-stage protocol, smart contract risks and potential platform updates could affect position management and funding calculations. The 0.05% taker fee structure, while competitive, can erode profits from small funding rate differentials typical in mature markets. Traders should monitor SUI's on-chain activity and ecosystem developments, as these directly impact funding rate sustainability on this Layer 1 focused perpetual contract."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are SUI funding rates calculated on RabbitX?","answer":"RabbitX calculates and settles SUI/USDT funding rates every hour, providing more frequent settlement opportunities compared to traditional 8-hour cycles. This hourly mechanism allows for more responsive rate adjustments to market conditions and creates additional arbitrage opportunities for active traders."},{"question":"What are the trading fees for SUI perpetuals on RabbitX?","answer":"RabbitX charges 0.02% for maker orders and 0.05% for taker orders on SUI/USDT perpetuals. The platform offers zero gas fees for all trading operations due to its Starknet-based infrastructure with off-chain order matching, making it cost-effective for high-frequency funding rate strategies."},{"question":"Can I use cross-margin for SUI funding rate arbitrage on RabbitX?","answer":"Yes, RabbitX supports cross-margin trading which allows you to use your entire account balance as collateral for SUI perpetual positions. This feature is particularly useful for funding rate arbitrage strategies as it maximizes capital efficiency when managing multiple positions simultaneously."},{"question":"How does RabbitX's DEX model affect SUI funding rate accuracy?","answer":"As a DEX with smaller liquidity compared to major centralized exchanges, RabbitX's SUI funding rates may occasionally deviate from broader market rates. However, the transparent on-chain settlement via Starknet ensures rate calculations are verifiable, and the smaller user base can create profitable arbitrage opportunities for informed traders."}]}]
